author: Liam Deacon
title: ‘One in Five’ Danish Newborns Has Foreign Heritage, Syrians Largest Group
text: Young migrant holding a baby walks at the E45 freeway from Padborg, on the Danish-German border, heading north to try to get to Sweden on September 9, 2015. The migrants arrived this morning with a train from Germany and were placed at a school from where they fled.
